author: Daniel Palmer
title: Australian dollar soars clear of US73 to its highest mark in seven weeks
text:
THE Australian dollar has jumped to its highest mark in seven weeks as commodities rise and the US dollar is hurt by reduced rate hike expectations in America.
At 10.30am, the currency was trading at US73.12c, up from US72.85c on Friday.
The unit hit a high of US73.46c on Saturday morning, its highest level since August 20.
The gains were driven by a sliding US dollar as investors took a set against the potential for a 2015 rate hike on the back of Thursday's release of dovish minutes from the US Federal Reserveâ€™s September meeting.
A surge in commodity prices also aided the unit, with iron ore up 1.3 per cent, copper adding 3 per cent and zinc soaring more than 10 per cent.
